#MEM id=milestone source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/milestone/SKILL.md savings=15%
M||tx|---
M||name|milestone
M||desc|Drive implementation forward incrementally w/ automatic progress tracking, LOC monitoring, and milestone checkpoint creation
M||tx|---
M|Mile|tx|This skill is a core cp for implementing large features incrementally, providing transparent context through LOC tracking, tst execution, and milestone checkpoint creation when the 800 LOC threshold is reached w/o completion.
M|Skil|The |
M|Skil|- **|Works in chunks of 100-200 LOC per iteration
M|Skil|- **|Monitors total LOC count across the sn
M|Skil|- **|Executes tests after each implementation chunk
M|Skil|- **|Generates milestone documents at 800 LOC threshold
M|Skil|- **|Returns sc when all tests pass
M|Skil|tx|This skill is the core implementation driver used by `/issue-to-impl` and `/miles2miles` commands.
M|Phil|- **|Small, testable chunks beat large rewrites
M|Phil|it|Provide unobvious tc in and ds decisions you made during this chunk of implementation
M|Phil|- **|Milestone documents provide clear progress visibility
M|Phil|- **|Use lines of code (not time) to determine when to checkpoint
M|Phil|- **|** You are allowed to have some tst failures at milestones, which particularly means you **are REQUIRED** to run a thorough tst suite after each chunk of implementation, and before creating a milestone.
M|Phil|it|The milestone document will record the status of all the tests, inc passed and failed tests.
M|Phil|it|**Example**
M|Phil|- **|** 5/8 tests Passed
M|Phil|- **|** 6/8 tests Passed
M|Phil|- **|** Fix remaining 2 tests in nx milestone
M|Phil|it|You shd dynamically adjust our plan w/ the whole plan and the current status of milestone.
M|Phil|it|Did you incrementally finish some tests that were failing in the previous milestone?
M|Phil|it|Did you find some new edge cases that require new tests to be written?
M|Phil|it|Did you unexpectedly break some tst cases that were passing before? Is it related or unrelated to the current implementation plan?
M|Phil|tx|---
M|Inpu|The |
M|Inpu|tx|1. **Current branch context**
M|Inpu|- Br|`git branch --show-current`)
M|Inpu|- Mu|`issue-{N}` or `issue-{N}-*` (wildcard for backward compatibility)
M|Inpu|it|Issue number extracted from branch name
M|Inpu|tx|2. **Plan reference**
M|Inpu|- **|Read plan from GitHub issue using `gh issue view {N}`
M|Inpu|- **|Read from latest milestone document in `.tmp/milestones/issue-{N}-milestone-*.md`
M|Inpu|- Pl|implementation steps, file changes, LOC estimates, tst st
M|Inpu|tx|3. **Starting LOC count** (optional, for resume scenarios)
M|Inpu|it|When resuming from a milestone, start from the LOC count in that milestone
M|Inpu|it|When starting fresh (first milestone), start from 0
M|Inpu|tx|4. **Current tst status** (determined by running tests)
M|Inpu|it|You do not need to pass all the tests before creating a milestone, but you **MUST** run the tests after each implementation chunk to determine current status.
M|Inpu|- Yo|
M|Inpu|it|tst passed as expected by this chunk of implementation
M|Inpu|it|tst failed as expected by this chunk of implementation
M|Inpu|it|tst unexpectedly broken by this chunk of implementation
M|Inpu|it|What is planned to be worked on in the immediately nx milestone
M|Inpu|tx|---
M|LOC |tx|The AI ag **MUST** track LOC count accurately to determine when to cr milestones.
M|How |Use |
M|How |tx|```bash
M|Get |tx|git diff --stat
M|2 fi|tx|```
M|LOC |Extr|
M|LOC |- Pa|`X files changed, Y insertions(+), Z deletions(-)`
M|LOC |it|**Total LOC = Y (insertions) + Z (deletions)**
M|LOC |- Ex|`343 insertions(+), 25 deletions(-)` → **Total LOC = 368**
M|Accu|ct|Track cumulative LOC across multiple implementation chunks:
M|Accu|tx|```python
M|Pseu|tx|cumulative_loc = starting_loc  # From milestone or 0
M|Pseu|whil|
M|Pseu|tx|implement_next_chunk()  # im 100-200 LOC
M|Pseu|tx|current_chunk_loc = get_git_diff_stat()
M|Pseu|tx|cumulative_loc += current_chunk_loc
M|Pseu|tx|run_tests()
M|Pseu|tx|test_status = parse_test_results()
M|Chec|if c|
M|Chec|tx|create_milestone(cumulative_loc, test_status)
M|Chec|tx|stop_and_inform_user()
M|Chec|tx|break
M|Chec|if a|
M|Chec|tx|signal_completion()
M|Chec|tx|break
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Stop|- **|`cumulative_loc >= 800` AND tests are not all passing
M|Stop|- **|`cumulative_loc < 800` OR all tests pass (nearing completion)
M|Stop|- **|If very close to completion (> 750 LOC and > 90% tests pass), continue to finish
M|Stop|tx|---
